Shared testing framework		The Shared Testing Framework technique is a centralized approach for test automation, allowing multiple teams to utilize a common set of tools and utilities for web and mobile app testing. It enhances test development by providing a uniform, efficient, and scalable infrastructure, freeing teams to focus on creating impactful test cases. Its main advantages include uniform testing practices, increased efficiency through reusability, adaptability to diverse testing needs, and promotion of collaboration and knowledge sharing. This strategy is crucial for enterprises with interconnected systems, supporting a strategic, cohesive approach to testing and a sustainable testing ecosystem.
